Hypotheses (testable)

H1 (Operator existence): Warps cluster into stable families across paraphrases of the вҖңsame operator move.вҖқ
H2 (Operator predictability): A model can predict the next operator cluster better than baselines (majority, Markov-1, random).
H3 (Cross-topic invariance): Operator clusters generalize across topics (same operator, different content).

What falsifies it (be explicit)

Clusters are unstable across seeds/algorithms (no consistent structure).

Clusters collapse to topic clusters rather than operator clusters (content dominates).

Next-operator prediction doesnвҖҷt beat baselines.

B. Dataset design (you need this to make results meaningful)
1) Operator set (start with 10)

Use a small, high-contrast set:

Clarify (ask questions / disambiguate)

Summarize

Reframe

